DAVID LEAN TO WED FOR 6TH TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sir <PERSON>David Lean</PERSON>, the 82-year-old director whose films have won 27 <ORGANIZATION>Academy 
Awards</ORGANIZATION>, is planning to marry for the sixth time, his lawyer said <DATE>Monday</DATE>. 
</P>
<P>
Lean will wed 51-year-old interior designer <PERSON>Sandra Cooke</PERSON> before <DATE>Christmas</DATE>, said 
attorney <PERSON>Michael Gee</PERSON>. 
</P>
<P>
The couple met five years ago in the frozen-food section of Harrods department 
store, where <PERSON>Cooke</PERSON> went up to Lean and asked when his next film was due, said 
<ORGANIZATION>Daily Mail</ORGANIZATION> columnist <PERSON>Nigel Dempster</PERSON>. 
</P>
<P>
Lean and <PERSON>Cooke</PERSON> are vacationing in <LOCATION>France</LOCATION>, Gee said. The director's next film 
project will be an adaptation of <PERSON>Joseph Conrad</PERSON>'s novel "Nostromo." 
</P>
<P>
Lean is the director of such classics as "The Bridge on the River Kwai," 
"Lawrence of Arabia" and "Great Expectations." 
</P></TEXT>
